cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on path exploration based software engineering methods and proposes a new program analysis. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses undefined behaviors in programs and proposes a new analysis implemented in LLVM. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses SMT solvers to check the satisfiability of path feasibility queries written as a formula in the supported theories. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of symbolic execution based methods for proving properties about programs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the performance of solving path feasibility queries using SMT solvers for real world programs.
